library(tidyverse)

library(forecast)
## Registered S3 method overwritten by 'quantmod':
##   method            from
##   as.zoo.data.frame zoo
library(tseries)

df = read.table(file = '2004-2019.tsv', sep = '\t', header = TRUE)
df['X']=NULL
colnames(df) = c("start_date", "end_date","region", "state", "fuel", "num_gas_stations",
                   "unit", "avg_price","sd_price", "min_price","max_price","avg_price_margin",
               "coef_dist","dist_avg_price","dist_sd_price","dist_min_price", "dist_max_price",
                "coef_price", "month",  "year")
library(dplyr)
df = df %>% mutate(region = recode(region, "SUL"="South", "SUDESTE"="Southeast", "CENTRO OESTE"="Midwest", 
            "NORTE"="North", "NORDESTE"="Northeast"))
table(df$region)
## 
##   Midwest Northeast     North Southeast     South 
##     15429     36869     24702     17047     12776
df = df %>% mutate(fuel = recode(fuel, "LEO DIESEL"="Diesel", "GASOLINA COMUM"="Regular Gasoline", "GLP"="LPG", "ETANOL HIDRATADO"="Hydrous Ethanol", "GNV"="Natural Gas", "LEO DIESEL S10"="Diesel S10"))


df2 = df[,c("start_date" ,"fuel",'min_price'
            ,"max_price","avg_price","coef_dist","sd_price")]
df3= df2 %>% 
    group_by(start_date,fuel) %>%
    summarise_all("mean")

df3$start_date = as.Date(df3$start_date)

HE = df3[which(df3$fuel == 'Hydrous Ethanol'),c('start_date','avg_price')]
Diesel = df3[which(df3$fuel == 'Diesel'),c('start_date','avg_price')]
RG = df3[which(df3$fuel == 'Regular Gasoline'),c('start_date','avg_price')]
LPG = df3[which(df3$fuel == 'LPG'),c('start_date','avg_price')]
NG = df3[which(df3$fuel == 'Natural Gas'),c('start_date','avg_price')]
DS10 = df3[which(df3$fuel == 'Diesel S10'),c('start_date','avg_price')]

mergecols = c('start_date')
full_avg_df = merge.data.frame(HE,Diesel,by=mergecols,all=T)
colnames(full_avg_df) =c('start_date','HE','Diesel')
full_avg_df2 = merge.data.frame(full_avg_df,RG,by=mergecols,,all=T)
colnames(full_avg_df2) =c('start_date','HE','Diesel','RG')
full_avg_df3 = merge.data.frame(full_avg_df2,LPG,by=mergecols,all=T)
colnames(full_avg_df3) =c('start_date','HE','Diesel','RG','LPG')
full_avg_df4 = merge.data.frame(full_avg_df3,NG,by=mergecols,all=T) 
colnames(full_avg_df4) = c('start_date','HE','Diesel','RG','LPG','NG')
full_avg_df5 = merge.data.frame(full_avg_df4,DS10,by=mergecols,all=T)  
colnames(full_avg_df5) = c('start_date','HE','Diesel','RG','LPG','NG','DS10')

scaled_df = full_avg_df5
scaled_df$HE = scale(full_avg_df5$HE)
scaled_df$Diesel = scale(full_avg_df5$Diesel)
scaled_df$RG = scale(full_avg_df5$RG)
scaled_df$LPG = scale(full_avg_df5$LPG)
scaled_df$NG = scale(scaled_df$NG)
scaled_df$DS10 = scale(scaled_df$DS10)

  }

Drafts:

Base model

fit0 <- auto.arima(he.trn) (bestfit <- list(aicc=fit0$aicc, i=0, j=0, fit=fit0))

for(i in 1:3) { for (j in 1:3){ z1 <- fourier(ts(he.trn, frequency=800), K=i) z2 <- fourier(ts(he.trn, frequency=52), K=j) fit <- auto.arima(he.trn, xreg=cbind(z1,z2), seasonal=T) if(fit\(aicc < bestfit\)aicc) { bestfit <- list(aicc=fit$aicc, i=i, j=j,fit=fit) } } } bestfit

fcast.he = forecast(bestfit\(fit, xreg = cbind( fourier(ts(he.tst, frequency=800), K=bestfit\)i), fourier(ts(he.tst, frequency=52), K=bestfit$j))) plot(fcast.he) lines(he.tst,col=red) accuracy(fcast.he, he.tst)
